post_cb({"23866108": {"Id": "23866108", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>A nested class is one defined within another class, so both <code>B</code> and <code>C</code> are nested.  nested class is in the scope of its enclosing class. This is not transitive though - since <code>C</code> is not directly accessible inside <code>A</code>, but through <code>B::C</code>.</p>\n<p>The closest we find is:</p>\n<h3>9.7 Nested class declarations [class.nest]</h3>\n<blockquote id=\"so_23865908_23866108_0\">\n<ol>\n<li>[...] The nested class is in the scope of its enclosing class. [...]</li>\n</ol>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So, as <code>C</code> is not in <code>A</code>'s scope, it's not \"nested\" for <code>A</code>, but it is a nested class.</p>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "673730", "LastActivityDate": "2014-05-26T08:49:12.867", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2014-05-26T08:41:52.243", "ParentId": "23865908", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "673730", "LastEditDate": "2014-05-26T08:49:12.867"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_23865908_23866108_0": {"length": 6, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "section_id": 5925}}, "n3337": {"so_23865908_23866108_0": {"length": 6, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "section_id": 5697}}, "n4659": {"so_23865908_23866108_0": {"length": 6, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "section_id": 7399}}}, "23865908": {"ViewCount": "33", "Body": "<p>I'm interested in is the relationship \"A is nested class in B\" transitive? For instance:</p>\n<pre><code>class A\n{\n    class B\n    {\n        class C \n        {\n            //... \n        };\n    };\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>I.e. Is <code>C</code> nested in <code>A</code> in that case? I'm looking for a formal reason (reference to the standard) explained this moment.</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "23866108", "Title": "Is relationship that \"A is nested class in B\" transitive?", "CreationDate": "2014-05-26T08:28:27.500", "Id": "23865908", "CommentCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "OwnerDisplayName": "user3374795", "LastActivityDate": "2014-05-26T08:49:12.867", "Score": "1", "Tags": "<c++><class><nested>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});